    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nConsider the following lua script that simply opens two buffers in two floating windows with the first buffer contains `{ 'aaa', 'bbb', 'ccc' }` and the second buffer contains nothing:\r\n\r\n```lua\r\nlocal buf1 = vim.api.nvim_create_buf(false, true)\r\nlocal lines1 = { 'aaa', 'bbb', 'ccc' }\r\nvim.api.nvim_buf_set_lines(buf1, 0, -1, true, lines1)\r\nvim.api.nvim_open_win(buf1, true, {\r\n  relative = 'editor',\r\n  width = 10,\r\n  height = 3,\r\n  row = 1,\r\n  col = 2,\r\n  style = 'minimal'\r\n})\r\n\r\nlocal buf2 = vim.api.nvim_create_buf(false, true)\r\nlocal lines2 = {}\r\nvim.api.nvim_buf_set_lines(buf2, 0, -1, true, lines2)\r\nvim.api.nvim_open_win(buf2, true, {\r\n  relative = 'editor',\r\n  width = 10,\r\n  height = 3,\r\n  row = 3,\r\n  col = 10,\r\n  style = 'minimal'\r\n})\r\n```\r\n\r\nHowever, the first line of the `buf1` will be empty after calling `vim.api.nvim_buf_set_lines(buf2, 0, -1, true, lines2)`. The bug only occurs when `lines2` is an empty table, i.e. if `lines2 = { 'ddd', 'eee' }`, then the first line `buf1` will not be removed.\r\n\r\nPretty sure that the bug occurs somewhere after commit 898ef1835d, however I do not have enough time to bisect and target the exact commit that introduces this issue.\r\n\r\nThis breaks [dropbar.nvim](https://github.com/Bekaboo/dropbar.nvim) in some cases and might also be a cause of the recent breakage of [nvim-cmp](https://github.com/hrsh7th/nvim-cmp)'s select-next keymap, mentioned in #24897.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. Save above code as `repro.lua`\r\n2. `nvim --clean repro.lua`\r\n3. `:so` -> contents in the first buffer is wrong\r\n4. Close the floating windows\r\n5. Change `local lines2 = {}` to `local lines2 = { 'ddd' }`\r\n6. `:so` -> contents of the first buffer is correct\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nThe first line of `buf1` should not be cleared\n\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.10.0-dev-975+g3a876bd41b\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno, `vim` does not have corresponding API\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nLinux 6.1.38.12.realtime1-4-rt-lts\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nalacritty / kitty / konsole / wezterm\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nAUR",
